cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI 

The paper evaluates the usability of a modern PGP client, which involves both computer security (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspects. The study also involves software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of evaluating the Mailvelope software. The discussion of pain points and potential solutions touches on cyber security (cs.CY) and system implementation (cs.SI).
